  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, I love the way monsoon makes me feel cozy and relaxed. How are you feeling today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi Maya! Monsoon is so nice, yes. I feel calm too, but also worried about my exams. Today I studied hard—maybe I will pass? 😟  \nI cooked dal today, by the way. It was okay."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a good balance, calm and focused. Dal is a great pick, it's soothing and full of flavor. What kind of dal did you make?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was moong dal. I added some garam masala and green chilli. My friend said it was good, but I think I overcooked it. You know, like most medical students, I am better at books than cooking. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, moong dal is soft and easy to overcook, but it’s still comforting. Garam masala gives it a warm taste. What’s one thing you’d tweak next time?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe add less water? Or cook it for less time. I think I will try adding some spinach next time, like my mom does. She is a great kacheri!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Adding spinach sounds like a good idea, it adds freshness. Your mom sounds amazing at cooking. Did you try her biryani recipe yet?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not yet, but I plan to. My mom says I need to \"slow down and layer the flavors.\" I get excited and rush, you know? Maybe I will try it next weekend. What about you—do you cook?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get it, rushing makes things messy sometimes. My go to is simple, tasty meals. What kind of dish would you love to try making first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe something simple, like pani puri? Or maybe a classic like paneer butter masala. I like rich, flavorful dishes, but I fear I might mess them up. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Pani puri is fun to make and eat, all about balance of flavors. Paneer butter masala is rich and tasty, yes. Start with one you feel excited about. Which one calls to you more?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, maybe pani puri. It feels playful, and I can experiment with the filling and water. Plus, my brother loves it—so I want to make it perfect for him. But I worry about the spices… you know? 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Pani puri is a great choice, and exciting to get right for your brother. The spices can feel tricky, but start small, use what you have and adjust. Would you try making it this weekend?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, maybe this weekend. I’ll take it step by step. If I mess up, at least I’ll learn! 😅 Thanks for the encouragement, Maya. I need all the practice."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, just a tiny tweak, \"I’ll take it step by step.\" becomes \"I’ll take it step by step.\" That's exactly the right approach. What part of pani puri are you most excited to try first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I’ll start with making the puri. It seems tricky to get them crispy, but I’ve watched my mom do it many times. Maybe I can imitate her style. Fingers crossed! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it, starting with the puri is a smart move. Imitating your mom’s style sounds like a great plan. Will you ask her for a quick tip before you begin?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, I will. She knows I’m trying, so she’ll help. She always says, \"Puri is like music—needs rhythm and patience.\" I don’t know how she does it! 🤔  \nThanks again for talking, Maya. I feel more ready to try. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, rhythm and patience, that’s a perfect way to put it. Cooking and music both need a steady touch. What time will you start your first attempt?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe around 10 am, when I have time and calm. I’ll record the process, just in case! 😅 If I fail, I’ll laugh and try again. Thanks for listening, Maya. I feel hopeful! 🌤️"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You’re welcome, and 10 am sounds like a great time, calm and focused. Recording it is a smart idea, you’ll see what works and what to tweak. What’s your favorite part of cooking, even when it’s tricky?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I like the part where everything comes together—like when the smell fills the kitchen, and you know it’s going to taste good. Even if I mess up, that moment makes me happy! Maybe it’s my \"rhythm,\" like my mom says. 😊 Thanks, Maya! I really should go now—byeee! 🌦️"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You’re welcome, Aarti! That moment when the kitchen smells amazing is pure magic, no matter the outcome. Hope your puri turns out crispy and your day ends on a calm note. Tell me how it goes next time, byeee! ️"
    }
  ],
